snippet.textDisplay: Claire probably gets burned using oven mitts because she is left handed. It would happen to me all the time, and I'm also left handed. Oven mitts are OFTEN fully padded on one side (for right hand use) and not so much on the other. Left handed people put oven mitts on "backwards" where the back of the mitt is on the grasping surface of your left hand. So a left handed person grabs a normal oven mitt, puts it on their left hand (naturally) and gets a big burning surprise when tthey reach in the oven and realize too late that the oven mitt isn't made for them.

snippet.textDisplay: The way you avoid bad eggs is put them in water at least 3 times as deep as the egg. The egg that floats is bad, toss it. If you use floaters, you might too.
